The paper deals with the concept of competitive equilibrium in market economics, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and computational social choice (cs.DS). The paper also discusses fairness properties, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and economics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses a new tool for describing a CE as a subgame-perfect equilibrium of a specific sequential game, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
